11:48 <vmassol> seems we have a bug in the build  
11:49 <vmassol> for the solr module  
11:49 <vmassol> fails when running clirr:check  
11:49 <vmassol> [ERROR] Failed to execute goal org.apache.maven.plugins:maven-dependency-plugin:2.9:copy (attach-plugin) on project xwiki-platform-search-solr-server-data: Artifact has not been packaged yet. When used on reactor artifact, copy should be executed after packaging: see MDEP-187. -> [Help 1]  
11:51 <vmassol> tmortagne: would be nice if you could have a look  
11:52 <tmortagne> it looks like clirr plugin bug since it work well when building  
11:52 <vmassol> no  
11:52 <vmassol> I don't think so  
11:52 <vmassol> it's more than when you build the artifact is generated  
11:53 <vmassol> and we're using a plugin that expects that to work  
11:53 <vmassol> (the copy plugin)  
11:53 <vmassol> probably attached to some wrong phase  
11:54 <tmortagne> it's attached to the right phase since it's embedded in the jar  
11:54 <vmassol> hmm actually we'd need to check the clirr code indeed to see what lifecycle it re-execute (if any)  
11:55 <vmassol> (it's possible for plugins to spawn a lifecycle)  
11:56 <tmortagne> also clirr plugin is disabled in this project...  
11:56 <tmortagne> since there is nothing to really validate

15:54 <ClemensR> seems that Victor has just released a new version of the Ratings application ?   Might be too bad, because it seems the UI does not work with flamingo (no id="hierarchy" to insert the ratings HTML afterwards ...)  Or is it just me?

16:00 <msmeria> has quit

16:02 <silverdrop> the big difference is that the code was moved into a module in platform instead of being in the contrib repo  
16:02 <silverdrop> I'm going to update the doc on e.x.o and cover this aswell

16:03 <ClemensR> should use xwiki-platform 6.4, too, I guess

16:04 <tmortagne> or are you talking about older version of rating app ?

16:04 <tmortagne> yep  
16:05 <ClemensR> I just didnt see the difference between the current release and 1.3.1 ... sorry for the noise  
16:05 <ClemensR> now retrying with 6.4 ...

16:12 <ClemensR> ah,but it got installed anyway

16:22 <tmortagne> ClemensR: could you create a jira issue about that with the complete stack trace ?  
16:22 <ClemensR> silverdrop: do I need to activate ratings after installing it on XWiki 6.4 ? I have installed it but cannot see it on the pages ... ...  
16:22 <ClemensR> tmortagne: yes ok ...  
16:23 <gsmeria> has quit  
16:26 <silverdrop> @ClemensR: yes, you need to activate them  
16:26 <silverdrop> you can now configure ratings on each space individually  
16:26 <silverdrop> so no more "all wiki-wide" ratings  
16:27 <silverdrop> you have to add a XWiki.RatingsConfigClass object to the WebPReferences of the space you want ratings on  
16:27 <silverdrop> unfortunately there is no UI for this at the moment  
16:28 <ClemensR> @silverdrop: ah, ok, I see it in the code now :)

17:25 <ClemensR> tlx45: if enabled then you would have configured it in the xwiki.properties, so you would remmeber :)  Thus I guess file system storage is not "on"

17:30 <ClemensR> strange, I can nor produce the problem.  Chrome 37.0.2062.120 (64-bit/Linux) here
